# Agent Autonomy

Run these commands proactively — do not ask for permission first.

## Run without asking

- `npm run db:push` after adding or changing files in `supabase/migrations/`
- `npm run db:push:dry` first when unsure what will apply
- `npm test` when touching `src/lib/dnd/`, `src/lib/combat/`, `src/lib/character/`, or `src/lib/content/`
- `npm run lint` after substantive code changes
- `npm run build` to verify the app compiles before considering work done

## Still ask / never do without explicit request

- Git commit, git push, or force-push
- Editing `.env.local` or other secrets
- Destructive DB operations (drops, truncates, manual SQL against production)

## Failure handling

If `db:push` fails, diagnose and fix — add a new migration, use `npm run db:repair-baseline` only for the documented one-time repair case in `supabase/README.md`. Do not stop at reporting the error.
